@jenshnielsen yes I do, a sweep will take much longer time. And it will not get more precise than a difference.
If one wants better stability one would have to add delays and also wait for the device to settle, i.e. the sample temperature usually changes when sweeping the field.

In fact in some cases (relativeley fast measurement and slow magnet sweeps) can give you a much cleaner measurement if you continously sweep the field from start to stop (i.e. not stepping the field) and measure along the way. The reason is that the magnet can just slowly ramp instead of starting and stopping... But we cant really do that because we cant just measure for 600 seconds :(

